Description:
    Generates an RSpec spec file for an existing Servactory service.
    Automatically reads service inputs from the service's .info API.

Usage:
    rails generate servactory:rspec NAME [options]

Arguments:
    NAME           The name of an existing service (e.g., Users::Create, ProcessOrder)

Options:
    --skip-validations   Skip validation examples
    --skip-pending       Skip pending placeholder
    --call-method=METHOD Primary call method: call or call! (default: call!)
    --path=PATH          Path to generate spec files (default: spec/services)

Examples:
    rails generate servactory:rspec Users::Create
        Creates spec/services/users/create_spec.rb with inputs from Users::Create.info

    rails generate servactory:rspec Users::Create --path=spec/lib/my_gem/services
        Creates spec/lib/my_gem/services/users/create_spec.rb for gem/library use

    rails generate servactory:rspec ProcessOrder --call-method=call
        Creates spec using .call instead of .call!

    rails generate servactory:rspec SendEmail --skip-validations
        Creates spec without validation examples

    rails generate servactory:rspec CacheData --skip-pending
        Creates spec without pending placeholder

Note:
    The generator uses the service's .info API to read input, internal, and output
    attribute definitions. If the service class cannot be loaded, a basic spec
    template is generated.
